This paper discusses the use of citation algorithms to identify seminal scientific works in the field of biomedicine. The algorithms mentioned, Reference Publication Year Spectroscopy (RPYS) and multi-RPYS, are commonly used in the field of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of these algorithms to identify connections between foundational research and biomedical innovation, which could fall under the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
